                                <p class="input-group input-group-sm mb-3">

                                    <br />
                                    Please select your measures by choosing their Measure ID from the drop down menu under the associated header label. High priority and outcome type measures will be

                                    identified with a "Yes" next to the measure under the appropriate header label. Please remember that at least one outcome measure is required for the 2017 transitional

                                    year in order to obtain a score for the Quality category. If no outcome type measure is available, then a high priority measure can be used instead. <br /><br />

                                    The All-cause Readmission measure identified by Measure ID 458 will automatically be included in the quality performance calculations at the non-benchmark point

                                    scale of 3 for groups of 16 or more who meet the minimum 200 case volue. Please do not also include this readmission measure in the listing to the right if you meet these  specifications.<br /><br />

                                    After choosing each measure, select the submission method that was used from the drop down menu under the associated header label. Please note that the same

                                    submission mechanism needs to be chosen for every quality measure. If a submission method is accidently chosen that was not available for that particular measure,

                                    you will be notified of its unavailability under the estimated points header. Also, you will be notified under the needed rate for maximum points header if the benchmark for that

                                    measure and submission method will be based upon the 2017 reporting year's performance and a benchmark is not currently available to calculate points above the 3 point

                                    minimum.  A range of rates, or single rate, to obtain the maximum allowable points per measure per submission method will be provided for benchmarked measures.

                                    Topped out measures will also be identifed under the needed rate for maximum points column. Topped out  measures will be calculated the same as all other measures

                                    during the transitional year, but this will most likely change in the future.<br /><br />

                                    Once you enter the measure's performance rate under the associated header label, you will be provided its individual measure score under the header "Estimated Points".

                                    Review of the solitary rate or range of rates to obtain maximum points to determine if your goal should be to increase or decrease your performance rate for that

                                    measure. Solitary rates are only shown if you will need to reach 0% or 100% to receive 10 points for this measure and submission method. Those identified by a range of rates to

                                    obtain the maximum points will have the smallest rate on the left if your aim should be to lower your performance rate. Otherwise, your aim should be to increase your

                                    performance rate.
                                </p>
                            </div>
